                SystemC Class Library (Rel. 2.3.0)
                ==================================

This is the release of the SystemC 2.3.0 Class Library.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                IMPORTANT

1. This is the release of SystemC 2.3.0. This release contains bug 
   fixes for SystemC 2.2.0 as well as adding IEEE 1666(tm) compliance
   features.

2. This release is supported on the following platforms for which it has
   been well tested:
    o Centos 4  2.6.9-100.ELsmp #1 SMP Fri Feb 18 01:47:46 EST 2011 i686
      i686 i386 GNU/Linux, g++ 3.4.6
    o Fedora 14 2.6.35.14-95.fc14.i686 #1 SMP Tue Aug 16 21:30:14 UTC 2011
      i686 i686 i386 GNU/Linux, g++ 4.5.1
    o FreeBSD with GNU C++ compiler versions through gcc-4.2.2
    o FreeBSD 7.4 with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-4.2.1
    o HP-UX 11.00 with HP C++ compiler version A.03.39
      (Note: +O1 is the highest safe optimization level)
    o Linux (Debian 5.0.8) with GNU C++ compiler versions
      gcc-3.4.6, gcc-4.1.1, gcc-4.3.2
    o Linux (Debian sid/unstable) with GNU C++ compiler versions
      gcc-4.4.6, gcc-4.5.3, gcc-4.6.2
    o Linux (Debian sid/unstable) with Clang C++ compiler version
      clang-2.9
    o 64-bit Linux (Debian 5.0.8) with GNU C++ compiler versions
      gcc-4.1.1, and gcc-4.3.2
    o Linux (Redhat 6.2) with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-2.95.3
    o Linux (Redhat 7.2) with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-2.95.3
    o Linux (Redhat 8.0) with GNU C++ compiler versions gcc-2.95.3,
      gcc-3.2.3 and gcc-3.3.2
    o Linux (Redhat 9.0) with GNU C++ compiler versions gcc-3.2.2,
	  gcc-3.4.3
    o Linux (2.6.9-34.EL kernel) with GNU C++ compiler versions gcc-3.4.5
      and gcc-4.1.0
    o 64-bit Linux (Redhat 2.6.9-5.0.3.EL) with GNU C++ compiler versions 
      gcc-3.4.4 through gcc-4.2.2
    o 64-bit Linux (Debian 5.0.8) with 32-bit GNU C++ compiler version
      gcc-4.3.2 (./configure --target=i686-linux-gnu)
    o MacOSX with GNU C++ compiler versions gcc-3.1 through gcc-4.2.1
    o 64-bit MacOSX with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-4.2.1
    o Sun Solaris 2.9 with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-4.4.6
    o Windows NT 4.0 (SP6a) with VC++ 7.0 
    o Windows XP Professional SP3 (Cygwin 1.5.25) with GNU C++ compiler
      version gcc-4.3.2
    o Windows XP Professional SP3 (Msys 1.0.16) with MinGW32
      GNU C++ compiler version gcc-4.5.2
    o Windows XP Professional SP3 with Microsoft VC++ 10.0
    o Fedora 15 2.6.40.3-0.fc15.i686 #1 SMP Tue Aug 16 04:24:09 UTC 2011
      i686 i686 i386 GNU/Linux, g++ 4.6.0
    o Windows 7 SP1, cygwin 1.7.9 environment with Microsoft Visual C++
      2005 Express Edition SP1
    o Windows 7 SP1, cygwin 1.7.9 environment with Microsoft Visual C++
      2008 Express Edition SP1
    o Windows 7 SP1, cygwin 1.7.9 environment with Microsoft Visual C++
      2010 Express Edition

